Women in Valaparaiso, Chile celebrate the approval of a national referendum authorizing a rewrite of the nationâ€™s constitution.REUTERS/Rodrigo Garrido The draft constitution enshrines a number of new rights and freedoms such as free higher education, universal access to healthcare, reproductive rights, pensions, indigenous and water rights. The constitutional convention of Chile has finalized the draft of a new constitution that will soon be voted on in a national referendum. If approved, the new constitution will replace the current, neo-liberal, pro-free-market constitution. The referendum is going to be held on September 4, in which all citizens aged 18 and above must vote. Reposted from the Peoples Dispatch website